@startuml
' @id(DOM-PANEL-LAYOUT)
' @desc(DOM-PANEL-LAYOUT, "Layout state of the two side panels: whether the left MODELS rail and right MODEL CONTEXT panel are collapsed, plus the sliver width kept so a collapsed panel can be re-expanded.")
' Objective-side domain: collapse state of the side panels.
title Side-panel layout state (objective)

class PanelLayout {
  + leftCollapsed : bool
  + rightCollapsed : bool
  + sliverWidth : float
  + toggleLeft() : void
  + toggleRight() : void
}

note bottom of PanelLayout
  A collapsed panel still renders a thin sliver of
  width sliverWidth > 0 carrying an expand chevron,
  so it can always be brought back
  (see OCL-PANEL-SLIVER-MIN).
end note
@enduml
